Linux build
===========

The project can be built as a standalone Linux application with
PyInstaller.

Build dependencies:

- Python 3
- pip
- PyInstaller
- compiler toolchain
- ImageMagick development files and runtime libraries

Python dependencies are listed in `requirements.txt`.

A typical build flow on Linux is:

```sh
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
python3 -m pip install --upgrade pip
python3 -m pip install -r requirements.txt pyinstaller
./pyinstaller/compile-linux.sh
```

The standalone bundle is written to `dist/rmexplorer/`.

If you prefer running from source instead of building a bundle:

```sh
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
python3 -m pip install --upgrade pip
python3 -m pip install -r requirements.txt
python3 -m rmexplorer
```


Fedora notes
============

Install the system packages needed for a local build:

```sh
sudo dnf install \
    desktop-file-utils \
    gcc \
    ImageMagick \
    ImageMagick-devel \
    python3 \
    python3-devel \
    python3-pip \
    rpm-build
```

Then create a virtual environment and build the standalone bundle:

```sh
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
python3 -m pip install --upgrade pip
python3 -m pip install -r requirements.txt pyinstaller
./pyinstaller/compile-linux.sh
```


Fedora RPM build
================

This repository includes a Fedora RPM spec at
`packaging/fedora/pyrmexplorer.spec`.

The spec builds the PyInstaller bundle during `%build` and installs:

- the application files under `/usr/libexec/pyrmexplorer`
- a launcher at `/usr/bin/pyrmexplorer`
- a desktop file
- the SVG application icon

To build an RPM locally on Fedora:

```sh
mkdir -p ~/rpmbuild/SOURCES
git archive --format=tar.gz --prefix=pyrmexplorer-1.3.2/ HEAD \
    > ~/rpmbuild/SOURCES/pyrmexplorer-1.3.2.tar.gz
rpmbuild -ba packaging/fedora/pyrmexplorer.spec
```

If you need to build from a different source snapshot, keep the source
archive prefix and filename version aligned with the version declared in
`rmexplorer/_version.py` and in the spec file.
